 The map lets a deep link resolve its containing chunk folder directly instead of\n     * scanning folders sequentially; a missing or unreachable map degrades to null and\n     * callers fall back to the legacy folder scan.\n     * @returns {Promise<Object|null>}\n     */","meta":{"range":[3449,3818],"filename":"MainContainerController.mjs","lineno":114,"columnno":4,"path":"/Users/Shared/github/neomjs/pages/node_modules/neo.mjs/apps/portal/view/news/pulls","code":{"id":"astnode100028266","name":"MainContainerController#getIdMap","type":"MethodDefinition","paramnames":[]},"vars":{"":null}},"description":"<p>Lazily fetches and memoizes the build-emitted id→chunk map for this content type.\nThe map lets a deep link resolve its containing chunk folder directly instead of\nscanning folders sequentially; a missing or unreachable map degrades to null and\ncallers fall back to the legacy folder scan.</p>\n","returns":[{"type":{"names":["Promise.<(Object|null)>"]}}],"name":"getIdMap","longname":"MainContainerController#getIdMap","kind":"function","memberof":"MainContainerController","scope":"instance","params":[],"$longname":"MainContainerController#getIdMap","$kind":"method","id":13543,"neoClassName":"Portal.view.news.pulls.MainContainerController"},{"comment":"/**\n     * @summary Lazy-aware record resolution for deep-links.\n     *\n     * Probes the store for `itemId`; if absent (its chunk is not loaded yet), resolves the containing\n     * chunk via the build-emitted id map (one targeted load), falling back to expanding unloaded chunk\n     * folders (`childrenUrl` + `!isChildrenLoaded`) one at a time until the record's chunk loads. This\n     * is what makes a bare-id deep-link (`#/news/pulls/<number>`) resolve under the chunked store.\n     * @param {String} itemId\n     * @returns {Promise<Object|null>}\n     */","meta":{"range":[4388,5708],"filename":"MainContainerController.mjs","lineno":138,"columnno":4,"path":"/Users/Shared/github/neomjs/pages/node_modules/neo.mj